{"questionId":"9073838","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A planet orbits at a distance <em>d</em> from a star. The power emitted by the star is <em>P</em>. The total&nbsp;surface area of the planet is <em>A</em>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Explain why the power incident on the planet is</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>P</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>.</mo></math></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>P</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;the power received by the planet/at a distance <em>d</em> «from star»&nbsp;<strong>✓</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;is the projected area/cross sectional area of the planet&nbsp;<strong>✓</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073838","referenceCode":"21M.2.SL.TZ1.a.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Explain why the power incident on the planet is P4πd2×A4.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 8: Energy production","8.2 – Thermal energy transfer","Core","Topic 8: Energy production"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}